2
00:00:10,779 --> 00:00:10,895
ht

3
00:00:10,896 --> 00:00:11,013
htt

4
00:00:11,014 --> 00:00:11,131
http

5
00:00:11,132 --> 00:00:11,248
http:

6
00:00:11,249 --> 00:00:11,366
http:/

7
00:00:11,367 --> 00:00:11,484
http://

8
00:00:11,485 --> 00:00:11,601
http://h

9
00:00:11,602 --> 00:00:11,719
http://hi

10
00:00:11,720 --> 00:00:11,836
http://hiq

11
00:00:11,837 --> 00:00:11,954
http://hiqv

12
00:00:11,955 --> 00:00:12,072
http://hiqve

13
00:00:12,073 --> 00:00:12,189
http://hiqve.

14
00:00:12,190 --> 00:00:12,307
http://hiqve.c

15
00:00:12,308 --> 00:00:12,425
http://hiqve.co

16
00:00:12,426 --> 00:00:12,542
http://hiqve.com

17
00:00:12,543 --> 00:00:12,660
http://hiqve.com/

18
00:00:12,661 --> 00:00:15,661
http://hiqve.com/

19
00:00:18,685 --> 00:00:21,103
<i>ANNOUNCER: Grievous in retreat.</i>

20
00:00:21,187 --> 00:00:25,691
Before the battleship Malevolence could
<i>destroy an Outer Rim clone medical base,</i>

21
00:00:25,775 --> 00:00:27,234
<i>a Republic strike force</i>

22
00:00:27,318 --> 00:00:30,362
<i>under the command of</i>
<i>Jedi General Anakin Skywalker</i>

23
00:00:30,447 --> 00:00:34,867
<i>crippled the warship,</i>
<i>disabling its dreaded ion cannon.</i>

24
00:00:37,787 --> 00:00:41,957
<i>Now, the Jedi relentlessly pursue</i>
the Malevolence.

25
00:01:03,897 --> 00:01:06,774
Commander, what is the damage level
to the enemy ship?

26
00:01:06,816 --> 00:01:09,151
She's lost her primary shields
and stabilizers,

27
00:01:09,277 --> 00:01:12,488
but the ship is so massive, it can take
all the fire our cannons can give it.

28
00:01:12,739 --> 00:01:15,074
We must summon reinforcements.

29
00:01:15,158 --> 00:01:16,658
ANAKIN: That's why I'm here, Master Plo.

30
00:01:16,785 --> 00:01:19,161
Anakin. Were you able
to contact Master Luminara?

31
00:01:19,287 --> 00:01:23,165
Yes, Master. She's busy with a fleet
of Separatist reinforcements nearby.

32
00:01:23,249 --> 00:01:25,834
She won't be able to give us support
until she's turned them away.

33
00:01:25,919 --> 00:01:27,628
Then we'll have to make do
with what we have.

34
00:01:38,473 --> 00:01:40,516
We've lost our primary weapon.

35
00:01:40,642 --> 00:01:43,519
Uh, the hyperdrive has been disabled.

36
00:01:44,312 --> 00:01:47,856
General? General!
The forward engines are shutting down!

37
00:01:48,149 --> 00:01:49,525
Impossible!

38
00:01:55,156 --> 00:01:56,573
Admiral, status report.

39
00:01:56,699 --> 00:01:58,659
YULAREN: They're not attempting
to jump to hyperspace.

40
00:01:58,701 --> 00:02:00,577
Their hyperdrive must be damaged.

41
00:02:00,703 --> 00:02:01,745
This is our chance.

42
00:02:01,871 --> 00:02:05,374
All ships target the bridge.
Maximum firepower!

43
00:02:14,926 --> 00:02:19,054
It has sustained extensive damage.

44
00:02:19,097 --> 00:02:23,976
<i>General, I have arranged a trap which</i>
<i>will give you an advantage over the Jedi.</i>

45
00:02:24,227 --> 00:02:26,562
I assure you, that is unnecessary.

46
00:02:26,646 --> 00:02:32,401
<i>Do not compound your failure this day</i>
<i>by allowing our prize warship to fall.</i>

47
00:02:32,485 --> 00:02:36,738
My lord, they will never capture me
or this ship.

48
00:02:36,781 --> 00:02:41,118
<i>Heading towards you</i>
<i>is a very important Galactic senator.</i>

49
00:02:41,244 --> 00:02:46,081
<i>With her as your hostage,</i>
<i>they will call off their attack.</i>

50
00:02:46,166 --> 00:02:48,417
As you wish, my lord.

51
00:02:52,005 --> 00:02:57,176
My lady, are you sure the information
from Chancellor Palpatine is reliable?

52
00:02:57,427 --> 00:02:59,261
Yes. It was secretly given to him

53
00:02:59,345 --> 00:03:02,347
by the supreme executive
of the Banking Clan himself.

54
00:03:02,432 --> 00:03:06,935
If they leave the Separatist alliance, it will
go a long way to shortening this war.

55
00:03:08,438 --> 00:03:10,480
We're approaching the system now.

56
00:03:13,193 --> 00:03:14,276
(EXCLAIMS)

57
00:03:14,360 --> 00:03:15,569
My goodness!

58
00:03:16,487 --> 00:03:20,574
This isn't right! That's a droid warship!
We're in the middle of a battle!

59
00:03:21,993 --> 00:03:25,037
Sir, we're scanning
a small ship off our bow.

60
00:03:25,205 --> 00:03:28,457
Good. Our hostage has arrived.

61
00:03:33,338 --> 00:03:36,590
Master, I'm picking up a signal
near the enemy vessel.

62
00:03:36,674 --> 00:03:38,467
Something just came out of hyperspace.

63
00:03:38,551 --> 00:03:43,388
-Enemy reinforcements?
-No. It looks like a Naboo ship.

64
00:03:43,890 --> 00:03:47,976
Gunners! Stand down!
What in blazes are they doing out here?

65
00:03:48,061 --> 00:03:49,645
Ahsoka, contact that ship!

66
00:03:52,398 --> 00:03:56,235
<i>-AHSOKA: Naboo cruiser! Identify yourself!</i>
-This is Senator Amidala.

67
00:03:56,319 --> 00:04:00,489
-Padmé? What are you doing out here?
<i>-I was sent on a special mission.</i>

68
00:04:00,573 --> 00:04:03,242
<i>The Senate was told the Banking Clan</i>
<i>wanted to negotiate a treaty.</i>

69
00:04:03,409 --> 00:04:05,118
Get out of there as fast as you can!

70
00:04:05,787 --> 00:04:08,121
Activate the tractor beam!

71
00:04:10,250 --> 00:04:14,044
-Have we been hit?
-I'm afraid it's much worse than that.

72
00:04:16,506 --> 00:04:17,881
Padmé, what's happening?

73
00:04:17,966 --> 00:04:20,676
<i>I'm being pulled inside the droid cruiser</i>
<i>by a tractor beam.</i>

74
00:04:27,976 --> 00:04:30,435
<i>I will not be made</i>
<i>a Separatist bargaining chip.</i>

75
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:35,190
<i>Continue your attack!</i>
<i>You must destroy this monstrous ship!</i>

76
00:04:39,904 --> 00:04:42,781
Admiral, order our ships to stop firing.

77
00:04:55,503 --> 00:04:57,838
It does not look safe out there, my lady.

78
00:04:57,922 --> 00:05:02,092
I see now this whole thing was a trap,
and I'm afraid I walked right into it.

79
00:05:02,427 --> 00:05:05,595
Sir, the Republic cruisers
have halted their attack.

80
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:10,142
Jedi are so predictable.
Get the repair team up here.

81
00:05:10,226 --> 00:05:15,314
Continue working on the hyperdrive.
I'm going down to the main hangar.

82
00:05:21,571 --> 00:05:25,365
This ship must be returned
to Count Dooku intact.

83
00:05:32,290 --> 00:05:34,875
There is no room for failure.

84
00:05:40,631 --> 00:05:41,757
(BEEPING)

85
00:05:41,841 --> 00:05:44,259
Come on.
I've overloaded the power system.

86
00:05:44,344 --> 00:05:45,844
Oh! We're doomed.

87
00:05:47,513 --> 00:05:51,433
-Where do you think you're going?
-Somebody has to save her skin.

88
00:05:51,517 --> 00:05:53,810
I thought you might say that.

89
00:05:54,395 --> 00:05:58,982
There he goes again,
craving adventure and excitement.

90
00:05:59,067 --> 00:06:00,901
You get used to it.

91
00:06:04,906 --> 00:06:06,740
Come on, Threepio! Hurry!

92
00:06:07,283 --> 00:06:10,202
Hurrying, my lady.
I'm not sure this is such a good idea.

93
00:06:24,801 --> 00:06:27,219
GRIEVOUS: You two! Come with me.

94
00:06:33,976 --> 00:06:36,186
(ALARM SOUNDING)

95
00:06:37,063 --> 00:06:40,565
Looks like the engines
are set to destroy themselves.

96
00:06:40,733 --> 00:06:42,359
GRIEVOUS: Get out of my way!

97
00:06:42,485 --> 00:06:44,319
Hey! That's just rude.

98
00:06:52,161 --> 00:06:54,496
DROID 1: Watch what you're doing
with that thing!

99
00:06:54,580 --> 00:06:55,705
DROID 2: Oh, pshaw!

100
00:06:55,832 --> 00:06:56,832
(DROID SCREAMING)

101
00:07:02,422 --> 00:07:05,882
Sound the alarm!
We have stowaways onboard!

102
00:07:13,182 --> 00:07:17,018
I trust you've already formulated
a brilliant plan to rescue the Senator?

103
00:07:17,061 --> 00:07:19,062
As a matter of fact, I have.

104
00:07:19,188 --> 00:07:23,358
But do we have a plan B?
Every operation needs a backup, Anakin.

105
00:07:23,401 --> 00:07:25,569
I don't have a backup. Yet.

106
00:07:25,695 --> 00:07:27,737
But I do have a plan
for getting on that ship.

107
00:07:27,864 --> 00:07:29,197
Really?

108
00:07:29,240 --> 00:07:31,533
The enemy's sensors
are obviously damaged,

109
00:07:31,576 --> 00:07:34,619
so we'll sneak in behind them
and dock at the emergency airlock.

110
00:07:34,704 --> 00:07:36,204
That's your plan?

111
00:07:36,247 --> 00:07:38,915
Just fly there, land,
hope they don't spot us,

112
00:07:39,041 --> 00:07:40,750
and walk in the door?

113
00:07:40,877 --> 00:07:41,960
Basically.

114
00:07:42,044 --> 00:07:44,796
Oh! Brilliant. Let's get going.

115
00:08:00,897 --> 00:08:03,648
C-3PO: Pardon me,
but might I suggest we keep moving?

116
00:08:03,733 --> 00:08:06,109
I think I hear battle droids approaching.

117
00:08:06,444 --> 00:08:11,698
But we also need to contact the fleet.
If I can just get this comm panel working...

118
00:08:15,036 --> 00:08:18,079
My lady, I'm afraid I was right.

119
00:08:23,252 --> 00:08:25,587
<i>-DROID: Uh, General?</i>
-What?

120
00:08:25,630 --> 00:08:28,757
<i>The damage to the hyperdrive</i>
<i>was not as bad as we first thought.</i>

121
00:08:28,883 --> 00:08:31,134
<i>We should be able</i>
<i>to get underway again shortly.</i>

122
00:08:31,260 --> 00:08:33,428
I must inform Count Dooku.

123
00:08:33,554 --> 00:08:40,101
Stay here. Continue the search.
Find the stowaway and bring him to me.

124
00:08:40,144 --> 00:08:41,937
Roger, roger.

125
00:09:02,416 --> 00:09:04,626
OBI-WAN: If they spot us,
we'll be pulverized.

126
00:09:04,835 --> 00:09:08,922
They're too busy repairing the ship.
They don't have time to notice us.

127
00:09:09,298 --> 00:09:12,467
Subtlety has never been
one of your strong points, Anakin.

128
00:09:12,510 --> 00:09:15,762
Everything I know
I learned from you, Master.

129
00:09:15,805 --> 00:09:17,847
Oh, if only that were true.

130
00:09:25,815 --> 00:09:27,148
(THUDDING)

131
00:09:27,191 --> 00:09:28,275
(DROID EXCLAIMS)

132
00:09:28,317 --> 00:09:29,442
What was that?

133
00:09:29,485 --> 00:09:32,529
-What?
-That noise. Didn't you hear it?

134
00:09:32,655 --> 00:09:36,324
It sounded like a ship docking
at one of the emergency airlocks.

135
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:39,828
Your circuits are loose.
No one's crazy enough to do that.

136
00:09:40,454 --> 00:09:44,791
Anakin, you're crazy.
Spinning is not flying.

137
00:09:44,834 --> 00:09:46,334
But it's a good trick.

138
00:09:46,460 --> 00:09:48,420
OBI-WAN: We do not want to be spotted.

139
00:09:48,504 --> 00:09:51,172
-I knew it! It's them!
-Oh, no.

140
00:09:55,011 --> 00:09:56,094
You stay here, Artoo.

141
00:09:56,178 --> 00:09:57,178
(R2-D2 BEEPING SOFTLY)

142
00:09:57,847 --> 00:10:01,099
<i>Another bold strategy by Skywalker,</i>
<i>I presume?</i>

143
00:10:01,183 --> 00:10:02,684
That's my master.

144
00:10:02,810 --> 00:10:04,477
Once they make it off that ship,

145
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:07,606
we'll need reinforcements
to finish off the enemy.

146
00:10:07,690 --> 00:10:09,441
<i>I am on my way, Master Plo.</i>

147
00:10:09,525 --> 00:10:12,485
We're receiving a transmission
from inside the Malevolence.

148
00:10:12,528 --> 00:10:13,778
I believe it's the Senator.

149
00:10:15,990 --> 00:10:17,198
-Yes?
<i>-AHSOKA: Master,</i>

150
00:10:17,325 --> 00:10:18,450
<i>we've found the Senator.</i>

151
00:10:18,534 --> 00:10:19,659
<i>I'm patching her through.</i>

152
00:10:19,702 --> 00:10:21,119
-Padmé!
<i>-PADMÉ: Anakin!</i>

153
00:10:21,203 --> 00:10:23,997
<i>-Are you all right? Where are you?</i>
-On the lower levels.

154
00:10:24,040 --> 00:10:27,626
I'm fine, but I don't know for how long.
Droids are everywhere.

155
00:10:27,710 --> 00:10:29,669
Obi-Wan and I are onboard, too.

156
00:10:29,712 --> 00:10:31,713
What? What are you doing here?

157
00:10:31,839 --> 00:10:35,800
We came to get you off this ship.
Ahsoka, how can we get to the Senator?

158
00:10:36,302 --> 00:10:40,722
According to our scans, there seems to be
a large open area in the center of the ship.

159
00:10:40,848 --> 00:10:42,849
It should be halfway
between the two of you.

160
00:10:43,309 --> 00:10:45,560
We're on our way.
Did you hear that, Padmé?

161
00:10:45,686 --> 00:10:47,228
I'll be there.

162
00:10:52,735 --> 00:10:56,071
DROID: General, we just detected
an unauthorized communication

163
00:10:56,155 --> 00:10:57,739
coming from within the ship.

164
00:10:57,823 --> 00:10:59,407
What did it say?

165
00:10:59,533 --> 00:11:04,537
Well... We don't know.
We didn't catch it in time.

166
00:11:04,580 --> 00:11:05,705
(GRIEVOUS EXCLAIMS ANGRILY)

167
00:11:05,748 --> 00:11:12,087
Monitor all internal communications!
I want that senator on this bridge!

168
00:11:19,261 --> 00:11:23,223
-I don't see her, Anakin.
-She's here, Master. I sense it.

169
00:11:28,354 --> 00:11:31,272
This is where
we're supposed to meet them.

170
00:11:32,024 --> 00:11:33,775
He's probably late again.

171
00:11:33,859 --> 00:11:36,778
C-3PO: But we do have company
of another sort.

172
00:11:36,862 --> 00:11:38,238
Blast them!

173
00:11:41,450 --> 00:11:42,909
There!

174
00:11:51,043 --> 00:11:52,627
Look! Jedi!

175
00:11:52,712 --> 00:11:54,462
-Fire!
-No! Wait!

176
00:11:57,466 --> 00:11:58,967
I knew that was a bad idea.

177
00:12:00,720 --> 00:12:01,970
Jump!

178
00:12:03,472 --> 00:12:04,973
C-3PO: Who? Me?

179
00:12:06,058 --> 00:12:07,600
(C-3PO SCREAMING)

180
00:12:10,479 --> 00:12:11,646
ANAKIN: Padmé!

181
00:12:16,318 --> 00:12:17,360
Anakin!

182
00:12:24,452 --> 00:12:26,828
There they are! Fire!

183
00:12:31,375 --> 00:12:32,667
The bridge is out!

184
00:12:32,710 --> 00:12:34,836
Jump to me! I'll use the Force.

185
00:12:34,879 --> 00:12:36,796
You have to trust me!

186
00:12:40,801 --> 00:12:42,010
I've got you!

187
00:12:42,136 --> 00:12:45,346
Nice catch! I'll fetch the droid!

188
00:12:49,852 --> 00:12:54,189
-Oh, the things you do to get me alone.
-Stop talking.

189
00:12:59,195 --> 00:13:01,321
Oh! What is going on?

190
00:13:09,663 --> 00:13:12,373
Stop me! Please!

191
00:13:12,875 --> 00:13:15,001
Blast! That's not good.

192
00:13:16,045 --> 00:13:18,421
Anakin, I got separated from your droid.

193
00:13:18,547 --> 00:13:19,881
Threepio!

194
00:13:20,007 --> 00:13:22,717
I'll take care of it.
We'll meet you back at The Twilight.

195
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:25,720
No! We can't leave yet.
I overheard Grievous.

196
00:13:25,763 --> 00:13:27,388
Their hyperdrive is almost repaired.

197
00:13:27,515 --> 00:13:29,390
I'm already headed in that direction.

198
00:13:29,433 --> 00:13:33,269
So, I'll make certain that
the hyperdrive stays offline.

199
00:13:33,395 --> 00:13:35,063
(LAUGHING)

200
00:13:35,147 --> 00:13:38,942
We'll see about that, Jedi. Come with me!

201
00:13:39,235 --> 00:13:40,568
I'm getting you out of here.

202
00:13:40,653 --> 00:13:43,238
Artoo? I need you
to help me find Threepio.

203
00:13:43,322 --> 00:13:44,572
He's on the rail jet.

204
00:13:44,657 --> 00:13:45,740
<i>(R2-D2 BEEPING)</i>

205
00:13:45,825 --> 00:13:47,617
I know. I know. He does.

206
00:13:47,743 --> 00:13:50,912
Look, just find him for me,
and I'll be there soon.

207
00:13:55,918 --> 00:14:00,129
Someone stop this contraption, please!

208
00:14:03,509 --> 00:14:04,592
C-3PO: Oh!

209
00:14:05,636 --> 00:14:08,304
Well, I suppose I did ask for that.

210
00:14:25,865 --> 00:14:27,657
(LAUGHING)

211
00:14:30,369 --> 00:14:32,120
Hello, there.

212
00:14:37,793 --> 00:14:43,965
General Kenobi, did you really think
I would leave the hyperdrive unguarded?

213
00:14:44,216 --> 00:14:47,677
Anything is possible.
You haven't exactly impressed me today.

214
00:14:48,012 --> 00:14:49,304
(LAUGHS SCORNFULLY)

215
00:14:49,388 --> 00:14:50,680
Kill him.

216
00:15:21,337 --> 00:15:22,670
That was impressive.

217
00:15:22,755 --> 00:15:23,922
(SNARLS)

218
00:15:24,006 --> 00:15:28,509
Guard the hyperdrive!
I will deal with this Jedi myself.

219
00:15:37,686 --> 00:15:39,938
Obi-Wan! Come in, Obi-Wan!

220
00:15:40,022 --> 00:15:42,607
<i>OBI-WAN: Anakin!</i>
<i>I'm afraid Grievous is on to us!</i>

221
00:15:42,691 --> 00:15:44,567
Yeah, we noticed.

222
00:15:46,528 --> 00:15:50,323
We’ll rendezvous back at The Twilight.
<i>The fleet must engage...</i>

223
00:15:50,407 --> 00:15:52,867
Obi-Wan? Come in! Obi-Wan!

224
00:15:52,952 --> 00:15:55,495
-What's wrong?
-They're jamming us!

225
00:16:04,797 --> 00:16:06,464
That might buy us some time.

226
00:16:06,548 --> 00:16:09,467
-I suppose you have a plan.
-Follow me.

227
00:16:11,637 --> 00:16:16,307
I do believe I'm lost,
in enemy territory and all alone.

228
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:17,642
(GASPS)

229
00:16:17,726 --> 00:16:19,644
Don't shoot! I surrender!

230
00:16:21,146 --> 00:16:25,900
R2-D2! Oh, my,
you are a sight for short circuits.

231
00:16:25,985 --> 00:16:27,193
(R2-D2 BEEPING)

232
00:16:27,277 --> 00:16:31,197
Master Anakin sent you to find me?
Well, what kept you, then?

233
00:16:32,032 --> 00:16:33,533
(R2-D2 BEEPING)

234
00:16:35,202 --> 00:16:37,787
The General is demanding a status report.

235
00:16:37,871 --> 00:16:41,541
-Is the hyperdrive repaired yet?
-It's almost done.

236
00:16:42,209 --> 00:16:44,043
I'll give him the good news.

237
00:16:44,128 --> 00:16:45,169
Uh...

238
00:16:48,465 --> 00:16:49,882
Anakin!

239
00:16:50,634 --> 00:16:51,759
(GASPS)

240
00:16:58,142 --> 00:17:01,519
Ever since I've known you,
you've been playing with droids.

241
00:17:01,603 --> 00:17:05,481
I used to put them together.
Now I only take them apart.

242
00:17:05,566 --> 00:17:07,525
So, where do we start?

243
00:17:07,609 --> 00:17:11,154
First, we need to get rid of these droids
so they won't know we were here.

244
00:17:11,238 --> 00:17:14,532
I'm going to hot-wire the ship,
give Grievous a little surprise.

245
00:17:15,117 --> 00:17:18,036
I guess I'll clean up the droids, then.

246
00:17:21,540 --> 00:17:24,959
AHSOKA: Our ships are in attack position.
Any word from Master Skywalker?

247
00:17:25,044 --> 00:17:28,421
No, the droids are jamming
our transmissions.

248
00:17:28,464 --> 00:17:32,425
-We need to give him more time.
-I'm not sure we can.

249
00:17:40,100 --> 00:17:41,893
(DROID SCREAMING)

250
00:17:57,284 --> 00:17:58,993
(GRIEVOUS ROARING)

251
00:18:16,845 --> 00:18:19,847
That ought to do it.
How's the housecleaning going?

252
00:18:19,932 --> 00:18:22,183
Done! Let's get out of here.

253
00:18:26,688 --> 00:18:28,689
I guess repairs are finished.

254
00:18:28,816 --> 00:18:31,692
-Prepare to charge up the hyperdrive.
-Roger, roger.

255
00:18:36,198 --> 00:18:39,534
Artoo, are you quite certain
the ship is in this direction?

256
00:18:40,035 --> 00:18:41,119
(R2-D2 BEEPING)

257
00:18:41,203 --> 00:18:42,662
This way looks potentially dangerous.

258
00:18:42,704 --> 00:18:43,830
(R2-D2 BEEPING)

259
00:18:43,872 --> 00:18:46,707
I know the whole place is dangerous!

260
00:18:46,834 --> 00:18:50,419
I suggest we stay here
and let Master Anakin find us.

261
00:18:51,046 --> 00:18:52,547
Threepio! What are you doing?

262
00:18:52,673 --> 00:18:55,550
Don't just stand there!
Let's get back to the ship!

263
00:18:56,218 --> 00:18:58,177
Power up the engines, Artoo.

264
00:18:58,262 --> 00:18:59,929
OBI-WAN: Hold the ship!

265
00:19:05,936 --> 00:19:08,062
I'll contact the fleet.

266
00:19:09,064 --> 00:19:11,399
Artoo, release the docking clamp.

267
00:19:33,422 --> 00:19:36,841
-Time for some clever tricks, Anakin.
-That's what I was thinking.

268
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:46,517
All batteries, open fire!

269
00:19:54,526 --> 00:19:57,445
You know, we have guns.
You can shoot back anytime.

270
00:19:57,529 --> 00:19:59,197
-I was just about to...
-I got it.

271
00:20:05,704 --> 00:20:08,206
She seems to know her way around.

272
00:20:13,086 --> 00:20:16,130
<i>General, the hyperdrive</i>
<i>has been completely repaired.</i>

273
00:20:16,215 --> 00:20:18,299
<i>Should we retreat to friendly space?</i>

274
00:20:18,383 --> 00:20:20,218
Engage the hyperdrive!

275
00:20:20,302 --> 00:20:24,096
I'll meet you
at our secret base in Sector 4.

276
00:20:24,473 --> 00:20:27,808
You heard the General.
Prepare to make the jump to hyperspace.

277
00:20:27,893 --> 00:20:28,976
Yes, sir!

278
00:20:41,531 --> 00:20:44,367
-Nice shot, Senator.
-Beginner's luck.

279
00:20:44,451 --> 00:20:45,493
(R2-D2 BEEPING)

280
00:20:45,577 --> 00:20:47,370
Pardon me, sir,
but Artoo's scan of the enemy's ship

281
00:20:47,454 --> 00:20:49,580
indicates their hyperdrive is activating.

282
00:20:49,665 --> 00:20:51,332
-Don't worry about it.
-What?

283
00:20:51,833 --> 00:20:55,002
DROID: Coordinates are locked.
Hyperdrive is engaging.

284
00:20:55,879 --> 00:20:58,673
Uh... I think we have a problem.

285
00:20:58,757 --> 00:21:01,509
<i>General, there's something wrong</i>
<i>with the hyperdrive.</i>

286
00:21:01,802 --> 00:21:04,512
I thought the hyperdrive was fixed!

287
00:21:05,180 --> 00:21:08,349
The navicomputer is heading us
right into the moon!

288
00:21:08,684 --> 00:21:11,102
Fools! Reset the navicomputer!

289
00:21:11,436 --> 00:21:14,021
Quick! Reset the navicomputer!

290
00:21:14,106 --> 00:21:15,147
(RAPID BEEPING)

291
00:21:16,400 --> 00:21:20,486
General, we await the Malevolence
<i>at the rendezvous point.</i>

292
00:21:20,570 --> 00:21:22,738
<i>Have you made your escape yet?</i>

293
00:21:24,950 --> 00:21:26,617
No! Reset it! Retreat!

294
00:21:26,702 --> 00:21:27,743
<i>General?</i>

295
00:21:28,870 --> 00:21:30,246
General!

296
00:21:35,377 --> 00:21:40,047
Transmission has been cut off, sir.
I think the General did it himself.

297
00:21:40,424 --> 00:21:42,091
-We're gonna die!
-Abandon ship!

298
00:21:42,801 --> 00:21:44,135
(EXPLOSION)

299
00:21:48,390 --> 00:21:51,392
I imagine you had something to do
with that.

300
00:21:51,435 --> 00:21:53,561
All part of the plan, Master.

301
00:21:53,645 --> 00:21:56,480
(ALL CHEERING)

302
00:21:56,504 --> 00:21:58,504
http://hiqve.com/

